				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fighting Advice<a name="18000"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 04 11:15 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree 100% BW is where I stayed for a long time, playing around and swarm-kiting, plus screwing around with the Wurms and stuff, testing my limits and all that fun stuff. If you want a good spot to solo at 52 try HK nobles too, you're going to kill FP faction and if you kill the bards there you'll lose Antonican League faction but that's super easy to bring back up. 
<br />
Edited to add this:
<br />
Check out Jaggedpine!!!!! The poachers are still good xp at 52, and they are easier to swarm than the giants in BW (In my humble opinion) because they never resist and if you swarm in the clearing by the tent you will NEVER get adds. This is where I learned to swarm and still a fun spot to go, plus there's the Burnoose of the Half-Breed there (HE Illusion). If you get bored of the poachers you can kill Griffons and snakes and such, just don't touch bears, cats or wolves if you like JP faction. You can also kill the gnolls for great xp till 56 or so, not the white Brell gnolls, but the darkpaw guys, theyre a blast to swarm. This is a great zone that's very forgiving, a fun place to learn and tons of room to run like a little girl if you're getting your butt kicked (I did plenty of that <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />)
<br />
</span></td>
